article.headline: Lipscomb 69, Mercer 64
article.story: MACON, Ga. (AP) -- Eddie Ard's 17 points sparked Lipscomb to a 69-64 victory over Mercer Friday night. The Bisons (11-11, 7-8 Atlantic Sun Conference) led most of the game, starting both halves on a hot streak -- taking a 7-0 lead at the start of the game and then hitting four of their first six shots in the second half to stretch a 35-30 halftime lead to 10 points. A 20-8 run enabled Mercer (13-9, 8-7) to take a 53-51 lead on a 3-pointer by James Odoms and a 3-pointer by Jacob Skogen gave the Bears a 60-58 lead later. Ard's two free throws with just over three minutes to play gave Lipscomb the lead for good, 64-62. Skogen led Mercer with 19 points, Ross Alacqua added 14 and Will Emerson 13. James Poindexter added 12 points for the Bisons.
